editorialNotes.standard: We love finding and pinning creative ideas, tasty recipes, and more. Pinterest’s wonderfully designed app is a constant source of inspiration, whether you’re planning a trip, remodeling your home, or finding something to wear. With a bevy of helpful features—from collaborative boards to built-in messaging—Pinterest is an exceptionally visual way to explore what matters to you.
editorialNotes.short: Get creative with your holiday decor.

editorialNotes.standard: Zillow can help you find the home of your dreams—one that contains all of your must-haves, is a reasonable distance from work, and falls (kind of) within your budget. The app offers resources for every step in the process, from attending open houses to picking an agent to understanding the intricacies of the mortgage market.

editorialNotes.standard: Daunted by having to fill out a dating app profile? Hinge helps you showcase your best self with conversation prompts (think “Two truths and a lie” or “Let’s debate this topic”) that create fun and flirty ways to engage.
editorialNotes.short: Stop swiping and start a great conversation.

editorialNotes.standard: More than just a dating app, Tinder has been updated to become one of the most engaging, fun, and social apps around. Of course, finding matches is still a huge highlight—but with smart group chats, an awesome Apple TV app, and Super Likes to go around, we’re swiping right on this one.
editorialNotes.short: Get faster matches with Tinder Platinum’s extra features.

editorialNotes.standard: Matchmaking app Bumble flips traditional social norms. Here, women make the first move. Some 50 million people have used it to not only find a date but also make friends and conduct business. If you don’t start chatting within 24 hours, the match disappears—encouraging you to actually talk to people.
editorialNotes.short: Find love, friendship, or professional connections.
